Find most significant bit set in a 32-bit word.

detaileddescription.para: This routine finds the first bit set starting from the most significant bit in the argument passed in and returns the index of that bit. Bits are numbered starting at 1 from the least significant bit. A return value of zero indicates that the value passed is zero.

simplesect.para: Most significant bit set, 0 if val is 0

briefdescription.para: Find least significant bit set in a 32-bit word.

detaileddescription.para: This routine finds the first bit set starting from the least significant bit in the argument passed in and returns the index of that bit. Bits are numbered starting at 1 from the least significant bit. A return value of zero indicates that the value passed is zero.

simplesect.para: Least significant bit set, 0 if val is 0
